text.tspan: shows where the row will be after a rotation
rank of letters in L and F
Rows ending with 'c' are in the
same order as rows starting with 'c'
* before rotation the rows are sorted
Therefore we can calculate LF, if
we know letter rank for a row in L and F
of letter 'c' in the F column
uses bwt(text) for full text index

flowRoot.flowPara: a position 'i' is the count of the letter 'c' upto position 'i'.
The Occ function is the most important factor in the speed of LF mapping implementation.
